OL,3,CWhat next for Iranian regime if its
OL,4,CSupreme Leader is killed?
OL,6,FArticle 111 of its constitution was
OL,7,Fwritten in anticipation of the
OL,8,Funthinkable: the sudden loss of the
OL,9,FSupreme Leader, the single figure
OL,10,Faround whom the political and
OL,11,Freligious architecture of the Islamic
OL,12,FRepublic ultimately rests. The
OL,13,Fprovision is explicit in its intent to
OL,14,Fprevent paralysis. "Whenever the
OL,15,FLeader becomes incapable of fulfilling
OL,16,Fhis constitutional duties," it states,
OL,17,F"a council consisting of the
OL,18,FPresident, the Head of the Judiciary,
OL,19,Fand one of the jurisprudents of the
OL,20,FGuardian Council... shall temporarily
OL,21,Fassume all the duties of the Leader."
OL,26,@vD@TOUxD@[O]yD@AOU}D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
